{"questionId":"19464","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The diagram shows the graph of the quadratic function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math> ,&nbsp;with vertex <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/b8efeb98a7356346d329f48e932622437d2e91d5.png\"></p>\n<p>The equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> has two solutions. One of these solutions is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the other solution of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure. It appeared in a paper that permitted the use of a calculator, and so might not be suitable for all forms of practice.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for correct calculation of the left symmetrical point.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)&nbsp; &nbsp;(C2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br></strong><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19464","referenceCode":"20N.1.SL.TZ0.T_11a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the other solution of f(x)=k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Quadratic function"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}